STRICTLY FOLLOW THESE COMMIT CONVENTIONS:

- Always use `feat: message` for new features. Never add "implement" or "add",
  write the feature right after feat:
- Always use `fix: message` for bug fixes. Never add "fix", write the bug right
  after fix:
- Always use `chore: message` for chore updates. Never add "update", write the
  chore right after chore:
- Always write short commit messages that are easy to understand and explain the
  changes
- Never describe every single change in the commit message, write only a general
  description of all changes
